---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const clickBenchUrl = "https://benchmark.clickhouse.com/";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Benchmarks"
  description="ShardLoom benchmark comparison now points readers to the public ClickBench leaderboard."
  path="/benchmarks"
  active="benchmarks"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Benchmarks</p>
    <h1>Use ClickBench as the public comparison surface.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      ShardLoom will use the public ClickBench process for broad OLAP comparisons. The old internal
      benchmark dashboard has been removed from the site so stale local artifacts do not read as a
      current public leaderboard.
    </p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button primary" href={clickBenchUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Open ClickBench
      </a>
      <a class="button" href="/field-guide/benchmark-methodology">Read methodology</a>
      <a class="button ghost" href="/field-guide/limitations">Review boundaries</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Public posture</p>
      <h2>No local leaderboard on shardloom.io.</h2>
      <p class="narrow">
        Local benchmark artifacts remain useful for engineering validation, but the website should
        not present them as current public ranking evidence. Public comparison belongs on ClickBench
        once ShardLoom submissions are reproducible and accepted there.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="badge">External</span>
        <h3>ClickBench is the comparison target.</h3>
        <p>Readers should use the upstream leaderboard for cross-engine OLAP comparisons.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="badge">Local</span>
        <h3>Repo artifacts are engineering evidence.</h3>
        <p>Checked-in benchmark outputs support development and validation, not standalone public claims.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="badge">Claim gate</span>
        <h3>Performance claims stay explicit.</h3>
        <p>ShardLoom should only claim benchmark results with a named dataset, route, format, and evidence path.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="badge">No fallback</span>
        <h3>External engines are baselines only.</h3>
        <p>Comparison surfaces do not change ShardLoom's no-fallback execution boundary.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
